      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@Pacerier 2^31 (Integer.MAX_VALUE - 8, approximate) * 2^2 (assume 4 byte int) = 2 ^ 33. But I think 64-bit system have at least 48 bit for their virtual address space. A portion of virtual address space goes to heap segment, so it seems the array in Java can get much larger than this size. Am I missing anything?"
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 201997,
        "reputation" : 2254,
        "user_id" : 448779,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 100,
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b71b71d82074f242b6799e70678a604b?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
