    "answer_id" : 78714153,
    "question_id" : 3038392,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>The whole numbers which have at most 32 bits in binary base are from <code>0</code> to <code>2147483647</code>. So, integer has limit up till <code>2147483647 = 2^(32 - 1) - 1 = 2^31 - 1</code>. Since, array index takes <code>int</code> as index, the indices start from <code>0</code> to <code>2147483647</code>. So, there can be <code>2147483647 + 1 = 2147483648 = 2^31</code> elements maximally.</p>\n"
